---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import { GITHUB_URL } from '../consts';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Who I am and what this blog is."
	pubDate={new Date('Jun 01 2026')}
>
	<p>
		I'm Hampton. I build and break things out of a Kubernetes homelab in Murfreesboro, TN —
		bare-metal nodes, a stack of self-hosted services, and whatever I'm currently nerd-sniped by.
		My day-job gravity is computational chemistry and drug-discovery tooling; the rest of the time
		it's infrastructure, automation, a game server or two, and the occasional rabbit hole I can't
		leave alone.
	</p>

	<p>
		This site is what the tagline says: anything on my mind. Some of it is technical — notes from
		the homelab, things I figured out the hard way. Some of it isn't. I'd rather write the post I
		wish I'd found than the one that ranks.
	</p>

	<p>
		Fittingly, the blog runs on the homelab it's often about: a static
		<a href="https://astro.build" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Astro</a> build, packaged into a
		container by my own CI and served straight off the cluster. Every post ships on a
		<code>git push</code>. Find me on
		<a href={GITHUB_URL} rel="me noopener" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
